The paper proposes a reinforcement learning algorithm that leverages ideas from linear bandit and kernel methods to learn a low-dimensional representation of the probability transition model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), systems and control (cs.SY), and multiagent systems (cs.MA).
